gnome-games 2.91.3
==================

Chess got a new option for showing the captured pieces. Quadrapassel and
gnotravex got ported to gtk3.

Shortlog:
Daniel Mustieles (1):
      Updated Spanish translation

Dr.T.Vasudevan (3):
      Updated Tamil translation
      Updated Tamil translation
      Updated Tamil translation

Edward Sheldrake (3):
      Changes for gobject-introspection >= 0.9.10
      Changes for gobject-introspection >= 0.9.10
      Changes for gobject-introspection >= 0.9.10

Fran Diéguez (1):
      Updated Galician translations

Gheyret T.Kenji (3):
      Added UG translation
      Added UG translation
      Added UG translation

Greg McNew (1):
      chess: Add an option for showing captured pieces (Bug #510732)

Javier Jardón (2):
      Use gtk_paned_new() instead gtk_[h|v]paned_new()
      gnibbles: Use GSourceFunc instead GtkFunction

Kjartan Maraas (1):
      Updated Norwegian bokmål translation

Thomas Hindoe Paaboel Andersen (11):
      gnobots2: delete unused file
      gnobots2: GTK_OBJECT is gone in gtk3
      a higher version of gtk is already required
      quadrapassel: gtk3 port
      gtk3 implies glib v2.27 so these checks are not needed
      Delete unused omf.make and xmldocs.make
      Update error messages
      gtk_statusbar_set_has_resize_grip removal
      gtk_dialog_set_has_separator removal
      gnotravex: gtk3 port
      gnotravex: fix flicker when moving columns

gnome-games 2.91.2
==================

In this release the default was switched to building with GTK3. Only aisleriot
will keep support for GTK2.
Games ported to GTK3 in this release: gnect, gnibbles, gnotski, gtali, and iagno.

Shortlog:
Andrej Žnidaršič (1):
      Updated Slovenian translation

Carles Ferrando (1):
      Updated Catalan (Valencian) translation

Christian Persch (3):
      gnect: Port to cairo and gtk3
      aisleriot: Sync prop-editor from gtk
      aisleriot: Sync prop-editor.c from gtk

Daniel Mustieles (1):
      Updated Spanish translation

Edward Sheldrake (3):
      gnibbles: Add doctype to background svg file
      lightsoff, swell-foop: Fix segfault in gtkclutter init
      lightsoff, swell-foop: Don't try to manually iterate GLib main loop inside inner loop

Fran Diéguez (1):
      Updated Galician translations

Joe Hansen (2):
      Updated Danish translation of the documentation
      Updated Danish translation of the documentation

Jordi Mas (1):
      Fix typos in Catalan translation

Matej Urbančič (3):
      Updated Slovenian translation
      Added sl for Slovenian translation
      Updated Slovenian translation

Matthias Clasen (3):
      gnomine: Use get_preferred_{width,height} instead of size_request
      libgames-support: Use get_preferred_{width,height} instead of size_request
      aisleriot: Use get_preferred_{width,height} instead of size_request

Robert Ancell (5):
      sudoku: Make last played strings more translatable (Bug #628161)
      sudoku: Remove unused translatable tooltip strings (Bug #628161)
      sudoku: Change grammar in error text (Bug #628161)
      sudoku: Make play duration strings more translatable (Bug #628161)
      sudoku: Make puzzle title strings more translatable (Bug #628161)

Takayuki KUSANO (1):
      Updated Japanese translation

Thomas Hindoe Paaboel Andersen (7):
      gtali: gtk3 port
      gnotski: port to gtk3
      gnobots2: various gtk3 fixes
      default to gtk3.0 and gtk3-ready games
      gnibbles: gtk3 fixes
      build: add gnibbles to gtk3-buildable games
      iagno: gtk3 port

Tim Horton (1):
      lightsoff: disable using Gtk theme color as button color (broken on Gtk3)

Yaron Shahrabani (1):
      Updated Hebrew translation.

gnome-games 2.91.1
==================

This is the first release on the road to a gtk3 based gnome-games. So far only
aisleriot and glines have been ported but the rest is comming.

To build with gtk3 use "--with-gtk=3.0 --enable-games=aisleriot,glines"

New dependencies:
GTK+ ≥ 2.90.0
RSVG ≥ 2.32.0
LIBCANBERRA_GTK ≥ 0.26

Shortlog:
A S Alam (1):
      update for Punjabi

