gnome-games 2.31.90
===================

In this release the port to cairo has been completed for a few of the games. In
aisleriot some parts of the code has changed license from LGPL to GPL 3+. Also
a few bug fixes and some translations.

Andika Triwidada (1):
      Updated Indonesian translation

Christian Persch (19):
      aisleriot: Add cairo drawing mode
      aisleriot: Fix build with gtk3
      libgames-support: Plug a mem leak
      aisleriot: Remove debug spew
      aisleriot: Add aisleriot_card_theme_paint_card()
      aisleriot: Use gdk_window_create_similar_surface
      aisleriot: Fix thinko
      libgames-support: Add games_preimage_render_cairo
      aisleriot: Implement cairo rendering in ArCardThemeSVG
      libgames-support: Plug a mem leak
      aisleriot: Remove debug spew
      build: Use right clutter-gtk API version for gtk3
      aisleriot: Simplify code
      aisleriot: Remove uncessary ifdef'd code
      aisleriot: Clip to expose region
      aisleriot: Don't optimise exposes
      aisleriot: Change drag mask drawing
      aisleriot: Remove useless check
      aisleriot: Go GPL 3+

Craig Duncan (2):
      Changed the range of lines from (1..20) to (0..19)
      Included the rot_next variable when getting the block positions for preview

Daniel Mustieles (1):
      Updated Spanish translation

Daniel Nylander (1):
      Updated Swedish translation

Thomas Hindoe Paaboel Andersen (3):
      [glines] Port to cairo
      [gnibbles] Store tail direction before reversing the worm
      [gnobots2] Use cairo to draw backgrounds

Xhacker Liu (1):
      Add Simplified Chinese help translation of gntravex.

lainme (2):
      Update Simplified Chinese help translation of gnome-sudoku.
      Update Simplified Chinese help translation of gnomine.

gnome-games 2.31.6
===================

Sudoku got tooltips for the buttons used in the tracker. Quadrapassels manual
was updated with the name change of 'bastard mode'. As always the awesome
translators have updated many languages.


